1
00:00:16,308 --> 00:00:18,144
Hon, can I have a bite?

2
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:25,359
Thank you.

3
00:00:33,826 --> 00:00:37,747
We can stop for a while,
so you can eat properly.

4
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:40,499
-We still have time.
-No need.

5
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:41,751
You know how your son is.

6
00:00:41,834 --> 00:00:46,130
He's always excited when it's time for him
to go see Teacher Sam.

7
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:48,883
Come on.
Let me have one last bite, please.

8
00:00:56,182 --> 00:00:59,310
Save the chips for later.
Have a sandwich first.

9
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:07,985
Hey, what are you doing?
Keep your eyes on the road.

10
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,821
Just goof around with your son later.

11
00:01:15,743 --> 00:01:16,786
I'm sorry!

12
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:22,541
-Are you okay?
-Are you okay?

13
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:29,298
I'm fine. Don't worry.

14
00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:37,264
Are you okay?

15
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,676
Sam?

16
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:17,263
Come in!

17
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:18,848
-Hello, Teacher Sam.
-No need.

18
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:23,477
So, you can get started right away.

19
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:27,022
Hi…

20
00:02:31,402 --> 00:02:33,487
Just have him finish his sandwich, please.

21
00:02:33,571 --> 00:02:36,115
Sure, no problem. Leave it to me.

22
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:38,492
I'll walk up the stairs with you. Come in.

23
00:02:44,832 --> 00:02:47,001
Matt will pick him up later.

24
00:02:50,796 --> 00:02:51,964
Okay, sure.

25
00:03:00,014 --> 00:03:01,473
Sorry, I forgot.

26
00:03:02,308 --> 00:03:05,436
Eli picked these out himself.
He said these are your favorites.

27
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:11,150
It's our send-off gift for you.

28
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:28,542
Eli doesn't know about it yet.
He thought this was just a normal gift.

29
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:29,960
Okay, sure.

30
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:33,839
Sam.

31
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:54,318
Hon, let's go.

32
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:43,867
Done.

33
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,709
-For me?
-Yes.

34
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:07,725
Thank you.

35
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:26,243
For what?

36
00:05:33,876 --> 00:05:35,502
What do you mean?

37
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:51,351
Why? Did I do something wrong?

38
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:57,649
I'm not leaving because of you.

39
00:05:57,733 --> 00:06:00,986
-No.
-But I still need you.

40
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:06,075
Who's going to teach me when Mama is busy?

41
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,789
You can do it alone.

42
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:18,337
You promised me that you wouldn't leave.

43
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:25,803
Eli, I'm sorry.

44
00:06:44,196 --> 00:06:47,241
Take this with you,
so you won't forget me.

45
00:06:56,083 --> 00:07:00,295
Out of everyone in Escondido,
you're my absolute favorite.

46
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:18,355
Just make sure you win!

47
00:07:54,892 --> 00:07:56,518
What are you doing here?

48
00:07:58,395 --> 00:08:01,064
Come on. Let's just wait inside.

49
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:03,650
I'm going to stay here.

50
00:08:03,734 --> 00:08:07,487
Matteo is late again.

51
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:11,241
I'll text Matteo, okay?

52
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:26,423
Where are you? Eli is waiting for you.

53
00:11:10,504 --> 00:11:12,631
What I'm about to do is painful,
but this is the right thing left to do.

54
00:13:37,776 --> 00:13:40,278
No pressure, but you guys
better be champs again today.

55
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:43,949
-Hurry up! What's the password?
-Give it to me!

56
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:46,159
-Wait. Okay, hold on.
-Film Papa over there.

57
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:48,870
There! It's starting!

58
00:13:51,206 --> 00:13:53,250
Go, Papa!

59
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,418
-Go, Pa!
-Go! Go, Ma!

60
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,212
-Go, Mama!
-Go, Jackie!

61
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:59,589
Go, go, go!

62
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:03,176
-Go! Go, Eli!
-Go, Eli!

63
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:04,886
Eli! Hey!

64
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:08,265
Hey. Eli, what's wrong?

65
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:11,935
-What happened?
-Anton, he's really hot.

66
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:14,020
-He has a fever.
-Is he okay?

67
00:14:14,563 --> 00:14:16,147
Anton, Jackie,
there's a nurse at the clinic.

68
00:14:16,231 --> 00:14:17,691
Do you want us to have Eli checked?

69
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:19,526
Let's stop for now.
Let's go to the clinic.

70
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:23,655
I'm okay. I just need to rest.

71
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:25,824
Are you sure, son?

72
00:14:25,907 --> 00:14:29,077
We can excuse ourselves.
They'll understand.

73
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,748
Matteo, get the medicine over there.
Give me the water too.

74
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:37,210
Take this.

75
00:14:39,921 --> 00:14:41,756
If you don't feel better,

76
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,425
we're going home
whether you like it or not.

77
00:14:52,684 --> 00:14:57,188
I'll be okay. I want to win.

78
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:02,944
Sir Jeff, please talk to them.

79
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:06,948
Let's just monitor him for now, okay?

80
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:10,452
-You good?
-You scared us.

81
00:15:26,968 --> 00:15:28,470
Is that a person?

82
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:30,680
Holy shit, it is a person! She's dead!

83
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:32,223
Help!

84
00:15:32,307 --> 00:15:33,850
Help! Help us! Please!

85
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:34,976
There's a body here!

86
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:41,107
Should we just go home?

87
00:15:41,691 --> 00:15:44,110
It's better if we're at home.

88
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:46,696
He just wants some ice cream.

89
00:15:47,906 --> 00:15:49,949
Wow!

90
00:15:51,326 --> 00:15:53,912
Eli, look. It's ice cream.

91
00:15:53,995 --> 00:15:56,247
Isn't this your favorite?
Cookies and cream?

92
00:15:57,499 --> 00:15:58,458
So good!

93
00:15:59,626 --> 00:16:01,294
Come on, eat. Hey…

94
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:05,382
Where's Teacher Sam?

95
00:16:11,179 --> 00:16:12,972
Come on. Eat this.

96
00:16:17,018 --> 00:16:19,354
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

97
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:21,648
-Here, I'll help you open it.
-Come on, eat.

98
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:26,444
-That was crazy.
-Oh, my god…

99
00:16:27,112 --> 00:16:29,864
Oh, my god!

100
00:16:30,407 --> 00:16:32,033
Hey, Eli…

101
00:16:32,784 --> 00:16:34,452
Oh, god.

102
00:16:36,371 --> 00:16:37,664
Jackie…

103
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:40,083
It's Teacher…

104
00:16:41,167 --> 00:16:43,586
It's Teacher…

105
00:16:58,685 --> 00:16:59,978
Samantha Ignacio.

106
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:11,114
Samantha Ignacio, a university teacher.

107
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,911
What do you think?
Did she jump or was it foul play?

108
00:17:16,995 --> 00:17:18,079
Could be an accident.

109
00:17:18,163 --> 00:17:21,666
But in all my years here in Escondido,
this is the first time this happened.

110
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:24,085
Hey, enough with the gossip over there.

111
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:27,338
-Focus on the evidence first.
-Yes, ma'am.

112
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:28,631
Yes, ma'am.

113
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:33,887
This has to happen
just when I'm about to retire.

114
00:17:35,180 --> 00:17:36,973
The Mayor will make this a priority.

115
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:42,187
-Reden.
-Mayor.

116
00:17:46,441 --> 00:17:47,734
My team is investigating.

117
00:17:49,986 --> 00:17:52,363
I don't want this
turning into an online circus.

118
00:17:52,447 --> 00:17:54,741
Photos are already spreading.

119
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:03,833
Everyone, calm down. Calm down, okay?

120
00:18:03,917 --> 00:18:07,420
No one posts anything.
We don't know what happened yet.

121
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:12,050
We're still not sure what happened.

122
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:13,301
Calm down.

123
00:18:13,885 --> 00:18:15,136
Please calm down.

124
00:18:33,404 --> 00:18:35,657
-Good afternoon, Mayor.
-Good afternoon.

125
00:18:36,491 --> 00:18:38,993
Our police are already
investigating this incident.

126
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,871
Let's wait for the results,

127
00:18:41,955 --> 00:18:43,915
and give the victim
the respect she deserves.

128
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:47,085
-Okay. Thanks, Mayor.
-Got it. Thank you.

129
00:18:49,671 --> 00:18:51,089
Do you get it now?

130
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:07,313
Eli?

131
00:19:07,397 --> 00:19:08,982
Ma, Pa! Eli's missing!

132
00:19:12,694 --> 00:19:15,196
Ms. Ignacio just filed her resignation.

133
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:18,241
She got a job offer
somewhere outside town.

134
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:19,701
Was it suicide?

135
00:19:20,285 --> 00:19:21,786
-Could he be there?
-You're right.

136
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:23,705
-Her face looks messed up.
-Bro, excuse me.

137
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:28,334
Have you seen a kid?
About this tall, wearing a yellow shirt?

138
00:19:28,418 --> 00:19:31,004
-No, bro.
-No? Okay.

139
00:19:31,087 --> 00:19:32,213
This is insane.

140
00:19:33,256 --> 00:19:35,550
I also read online that maybe…

141
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:38,887
Maybe Eli saw the video,
got scared, and ran off?

142
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:42,181
You really shouldn't have left him alone.

143
00:19:42,265 --> 00:19:44,142
Can we stop blaming each other right now?

144
00:19:45,935 --> 00:19:48,146
Pia, Eli's really not inside.

145
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:50,565
So, what now? Where do we go?

146
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:52,942
I'll go to Mama and Papa's office.

147
00:19:53,026 --> 00:19:55,361
You check the parking lot
and the main entrance, okay?

148
00:19:55,445 --> 00:19:56,487
-Okay, Matteo?
-Okay.

149
00:19:56,571 --> 00:19:57,864
-Alright.
-Hold on.

150
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:05,914
Matteo.

151
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:09,375
Go ahead, you go first.

152
00:20:09,459 --> 00:20:11,294
-Let's go.
-Yeah, I'll follow.

153
00:20:13,922 --> 00:20:17,383
-Matteo, are you coming or not?
-Yeah, I'm coming.

154
00:20:19,802 --> 00:20:21,346
See? Scary, right?

155
00:20:21,429 --> 00:20:23,473
Professor Carpio!

156
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:25,683
Have you heard about
what happened to Teacher Sam?

157
00:20:26,726 --> 00:20:28,478
Word's spreading that it was a suicide.

158
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:32,148
Have you noticed anything unusual
about her lately? Weren't you close?

159
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,903
We don't pry
into Ms. Ignacio's personal life.

160
00:20:36,986 --> 00:20:40,490
Sorry, but there's no
ill intent behind my question.

161
00:20:41,366 --> 00:20:42,909
Did you see Eli?

162
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:44,369
-No.
-No.

163
00:20:45,662 --> 00:20:47,914
Why did you even mention that?

164
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:49,958
-It's your fault.
-What? No, you said it.

165
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:51,084
You talk too much.

166
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:02,637
Chief, the car's confirmed.

167
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:05,473
The car outside belongs to Ms. Ignacio.

168
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:07,350
And we also found this.

169
00:21:10,353 --> 00:21:13,898
And there's a letter.
Looks like a suicide, right, Cortez?

170
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:18,736
He'll be the lead investigator
on this case.

171
00:21:28,454 --> 00:21:31,165
I know he hasn't even been here
a week in Escondido,

172
00:21:31,749 --> 00:21:34,335
but the order came
from the regional office.

173
00:21:34,419 --> 00:21:37,839
He'll also be the acting chief
until I have a replacement.

174
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:43,469
Just let it go.
Consider this his welcome to the job.

175
00:22:42,111 --> 00:22:43,780
Why the long face?

176
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:50,745
Drink your milk.

177
00:23:01,255 --> 00:23:03,049
See? You're happy now. Look!

178
00:23:10,181 --> 00:23:13,309
I wish I weren't like this.

179
00:23:14,602 --> 00:23:15,978
No.

180
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:19,816
Don't think like that.
You? You're special.

181
00:23:19,899 --> 00:23:23,069
I don't feel special.

182
00:23:24,028 --> 00:23:28,074
Remember your superpower?

183
00:23:30,201 --> 00:23:31,410
Family.

184
00:23:32,787 --> 00:23:34,789
-Fa.
-Fa.

185
00:23:34,872 --> 00:23:36,666
-Mi.
-Mi.

186
00:23:36,749 --> 00:23:39,836
Ly. Family.

187
00:23:43,631 --> 00:23:45,883
-Family?
-Yes!

188
00:23:47,468 --> 00:23:49,220
Very good! See?

189
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:56,978
That's you.

190
00:24:00,648 --> 00:24:03,359
Family.

191
00:24:49,655 --> 00:24:50,823
Eli.

192
00:24:51,574 --> 00:24:52,533
Eli…

193
00:25:45,419 --> 00:25:48,756
My cousin and I just spoke recently.

194
00:25:49,382 --> 00:25:52,134
She was actually supposed
to move in with us

195
00:25:52,218 --> 00:25:55,596
since it's closer to her new job.

196
00:25:56,347 --> 00:25:58,349
Was she okay the last time you saw her?

197
00:25:58,432 --> 00:26:00,476
Did you notice anything off?

198
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:02,728
Nothing at all, Mayor.

199
00:26:03,771 --> 00:26:05,523
She actually seemed happy.

200
00:26:06,232 --> 00:26:08,818
She even told me, "See you soon."

201
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:17,451
I know how much this house meant to her.

202
00:26:18,244 --> 00:26:23,082
It's the only thing her parents left her.

203
00:26:23,165 --> 00:26:25,501
That's why I was surprised when she said

204
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:29,672
she wanted a change of environment.

205
00:26:35,177 --> 00:26:37,013
Ma'am, if you'll excuse me…

206
00:26:46,856 --> 00:26:50,151
Is it possible
she was actually saying goodbye?

207
00:26:51,277 --> 00:26:52,653
You know, sometimes…

208
00:26:53,654 --> 00:26:58,701
you never really know if someone
is going through something heavy.

209
00:27:09,587 --> 00:27:13,507
I've combed through the whole house,
there's nothing else to see.

210
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,431
I'm still not convinced, Officer Soriano.

211
00:27:21,390 --> 00:27:24,852
You don't believe
Ms. Ignacio took her own life?

212
00:27:25,561 --> 00:27:26,562
Not yet.

213
00:27:27,313 --> 00:27:30,149
-Even with the letter?
-That she didn't finish.

214
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,402
It's called a breakup letter.

215
00:27:33,486 --> 00:27:37,073
I've written plenty of those
for my ex-girlfriends.

216
00:27:38,908 --> 00:27:42,161
We found antidepressants.

217
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:45,247
There's no signs of forced entry
into the house.

218
00:27:45,331 --> 00:27:47,708
No witnesses.

219
00:27:47,792 --> 00:27:52,755
At the lighthouse,
there was a meal prepared for two

220
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:54,423
that wasn't even touched.

221
00:27:56,926 --> 00:27:59,470
And did you notice the padlock here?

222
00:28:00,137 --> 00:28:03,015
It looks brand new.

223
00:28:03,099 --> 00:28:08,729
Are you telling me she decided
to change the locks before she jumped?

224
00:28:08,813 --> 00:28:11,607
And why not? Maybe she was being careful.

225
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:16,195
But people who are careful
don't just jump off a cliff.

226
00:28:17,822 --> 00:28:21,075
Her phone is missing.

227
00:28:22,326 --> 00:28:24,662
She had a date with someone we don't know.

228
00:28:24,745 --> 00:28:27,248
Shouldn't we be looking for him?

229
00:28:28,332 --> 00:28:32,461
Ms. Ignacio had
a tutorial session yesterday.

230
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:34,880
The student's name is Eli.

231
00:28:48,477 --> 00:28:49,603
Where have you been?

232
00:28:50,646 --> 00:28:52,982
I had to finish something at school, Pa.

233
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:54,817
How's Eli doing?

234
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:59,405
The doctors didn't find anything,
so they sent us home.

235
00:28:59,488 --> 00:29:02,950
His fever went down,
but he still has no appetite.

236
00:29:06,704 --> 00:29:07,955
Ma.

237
00:29:08,581 --> 00:29:12,209
Why are they saying
Teacher Sam was depressed

238
00:29:12,293 --> 00:29:13,961
that's why she committed suicide?

239
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,922
That's what I heard too.

240
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,884
Don't pay attention to them, okay?

241
00:29:19,967 --> 00:29:23,012
Let's wait until the police
finish their investigation.

242
00:29:25,306 --> 00:29:29,727
Anyway, we might have to find
a new tutor for Eli.

243
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:35,316
We lost a friend, Anton.

244
00:29:37,067 --> 00:29:40,446
-And that's your concern?
-But…

245
00:29:42,323 --> 00:29:44,700
aren't you going to accept the promotion?

246
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:46,327
What about Eli?

247
00:29:50,164 --> 00:29:53,125
We'll talk about it when Eli is ready.

248
00:29:54,043 --> 00:29:55,961
Let's make things clear, okay?

249
00:29:56,045 --> 00:29:59,590
No matter how busy I am,
my family is my top priority.

250
00:30:05,471 --> 00:30:06,931
Ma, someone is at the door.

251
00:30:13,479 --> 00:30:14,605
Stay there.

252
00:30:26,534 --> 00:30:29,328
Good evening, Mr. Carpio.

253
00:30:29,411 --> 00:30:31,163
Mrs. Carpio.

254
00:30:32,122 --> 00:30:33,791
I'm Manu Cortez,

255
00:30:33,874 --> 00:30:36,669
the lead investigator
in Ms. Ignacio's case.

256
00:30:36,752 --> 00:30:38,671
How can we help you?

257
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:41,757
Can I talk to your son, Eli?

258
00:30:42,716 --> 00:30:43,551
What for?

259
00:30:44,635 --> 00:30:48,264
He had a tutorial
with Ms. Ignacio yesterday, right?

260
00:30:49,056 --> 00:30:53,477
I just wanted to ask him a few questions
since he was the last one with her.

261
00:30:55,479 --> 00:30:58,357
Can you do it tomorrow?
You can come back tomorrow.

262
00:30:59,733 --> 00:31:01,151
I just need a few minutes.

263
00:31:01,902 --> 00:31:03,237
Just come back tomorrow.

264
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:05,656
Sir, Eli has a fever.

265
00:31:05,739 --> 00:31:09,952
Just come back tomorrow.
We'll cooperate with you.

266
00:31:22,715 --> 00:31:24,133
What about you, ma'am?

267
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:29,597
When was the last time
you saw Ms. Ignacio?

268
00:31:57,166 --> 00:32:00,836
I didn't notice anything
different with Sam.

269
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:03,172
We were just a little sad

270
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,799
because it was
her last session with Eli, so…

271
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:09,136
we said goodbye to her.

272
00:32:13,557 --> 00:32:14,642
Why?

273
00:32:18,771 --> 00:32:21,607
Sam was planning to leave Escondido.

274
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:23,609
She found another job.

275
00:32:23,692 --> 00:32:25,569
You know what?

276
00:32:26,111 --> 00:32:27,821
Eli liked her.

277
00:32:27,905 --> 00:32:31,367
That's why we tried to talk to her

278
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:34,703
if there's any way she can stay here.

279
00:32:35,871 --> 00:32:38,207
But she's decided.

280
00:32:38,874 --> 00:32:41,835
Did she mention
when she was going to leave?

281
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:50,719
What about you, son?

282
00:32:51,679 --> 00:32:54,306
You said you were the one
who picked up Eli.

283
00:32:56,225 --> 00:32:59,353
Did you see or notice anything different?

284
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,410
Eli.

285
00:33:15,327 --> 00:33:16,787
Come on. Let's go home.

286
00:33:18,205 --> 00:33:20,332
Come on. Let's go home.

287
00:33:30,801 --> 00:33:32,052
Come on. Hurry.

288
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:34,054
Matteo!

289
00:33:35,806 --> 00:33:36,932
Is Jem okay now?

290
00:33:40,477 --> 00:33:42,062
I'm just here to pick up Eli.

291
00:33:42,146 --> 00:33:44,690
-Thank you, Teacher Sam.
-I'm serious.

292
00:33:44,773 --> 00:33:48,777
If you don't tell your parents,
I'll talk to them myself.

293
00:33:50,070 --> 00:33:51,113
Understood?

294
00:33:56,118 --> 00:33:57,119
Let's go.

295
00:33:59,747 --> 00:34:01,915
-Okay?
-I'll see you.

296
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:14,845
I don't think so, sir.

297
00:34:23,604 --> 00:34:27,691
What about Teacher Sam's phone?

298
00:34:29,234 --> 00:34:30,736
Have you checked it?

299
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:38,243
We still haven't found it.

300
00:34:45,459 --> 00:34:46,960
Why do you ask?

301
00:34:54,885 --> 00:34:56,094
No reason.

302
00:34:57,888 --> 00:35:01,892
It's just that, when you need
information about someone,

303
00:35:03,268 --> 00:35:05,479
you'll find it on their phone.

304
00:35:08,774 --> 00:35:14,530
I saw it in documentaries
and crime series.

305
00:35:14,613 --> 00:35:16,281
Something like that.

306
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:20,077
Detective, why?

307
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:23,914
Do you also not believe
that Sam committed suicide?

308
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,501
I can't answer that yet.

309
00:35:27,584 --> 00:35:30,087
This is just a routine interview.

310
00:35:30,170 --> 00:35:32,339
I'm making sure
that all angles are covered,

311
00:35:32,422 --> 00:35:34,091
so we can determine…

312
00:35:35,676 --> 00:35:39,054
if there's a case or not.

313
00:35:39,721 --> 00:35:42,683
People are saying
that she committed suicide.

314
00:35:43,183 --> 00:35:47,229
It can't be. Sam wouldn't do that.

315
00:35:52,693 --> 00:35:53,694
No…

316
00:35:57,322 --> 00:36:00,450
Sam was very close to us because of Eli.

317
00:36:00,534 --> 00:36:03,662
We know her very well

318
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:07,958
for my wife to say
that Sam would never do that.

319
00:36:38,405 --> 00:36:39,531
Where have you been?

320
00:36:39,615 --> 00:36:42,326
I went to talk to the Carpios.

321
00:36:42,910 --> 00:36:46,163
Next time, don't act alone.

322
00:36:46,246 --> 00:36:49,374
I'll let this one slide.

323
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:52,920
I did it to make
the investigation faster, sir.

324
00:36:53,712 --> 00:36:55,464
You're probably still adjusting.

325
00:36:55,547 --> 00:37:02,054
If you don't want to have any problems,
I suggest that you do what I say.

326
00:37:02,137 --> 00:37:03,722
You mean, follow the Mayor's narrative?

327
00:37:07,309 --> 00:37:09,144
I know what you're thinking.

328
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:12,481
The Mayor is a good person.
He's not corrupt.

329
00:37:13,065 --> 00:37:17,569
He just didn't want to make Escondido
look like a dangerous place.

330
00:37:17,653 --> 00:37:19,947
On paper, this is just a crime.

331
00:37:20,781 --> 00:37:23,742
But in reality, the livelihood, trust,

332
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:26,745
and peace of our place is at stake here.

333
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:29,206
As well as his ambition
to run in the next election,

334
00:37:29,289 --> 00:37:33,085
and your goal to retire
with a clean record.

335
00:37:45,347 --> 00:37:48,725
Go talk to your son. I think he needs you.

336
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:24,594
I'm done.

337
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:06,178
Are you not feeling well?

338
00:39:07,095 --> 00:39:09,014
Are you in pain?

339
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:12,809
It hurts right here.

340
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:20,400
Like I can't breathe.

341
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:28,450
Every time I close my eyes,
I see Teacher Sam.

342
00:39:51,431 --> 00:39:57,604
I'm sorry you have to go through this.

343
00:39:58,814 --> 00:40:05,278
I want to tell you that it will pass soon…

344
00:40:07,697 --> 00:40:13,120
but I know it won't.

345
00:40:16,039 --> 00:40:17,374
But this…

346
00:40:18,125 --> 00:40:21,545
I'm here.

347
00:40:22,504 --> 00:40:24,631
Always.

348
00:40:24,714 --> 00:40:27,843
You have me.

349
00:40:27,926 --> 00:40:31,930
You have your family.

350
00:40:32,013 --> 00:40:34,099
Always.

351
00:42:11,238 --> 00:42:14,574
Sam Ignacio is an Elementary
and Special Education teacher

352
00:42:14,658 --> 00:42:16,701
at the University of Escondido,

353
00:42:16,785 --> 00:42:19,955
and one of the founders
of the Able Hearts Foundation,

354
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:23,959
a non-government organization
that helps persons with disability.

355
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:29,256
-I'm so sorry. Sorry.
-Authorities expressed their condolences…

356
00:42:29,339 --> 00:42:30,423
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay.

357
00:42:30,507 --> 00:42:33,760
Authorities are still looking
into all possible angles

358
00:42:33,843 --> 00:42:36,596
in the death of the said teacher,
Sam Ignacio.

359
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:39,057
Could this be a crime in Escondido?

360
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:41,393
The police have yet to issue a statement.

361
00:42:41,476 --> 00:42:43,979
-You need a refill?
-The police encourage anyone

362
00:42:44,062 --> 00:42:46,856
-with information on this case
-Can I ask you something?

363
00:42:46,940 --> 00:42:48,566
-to contact them.
-About what, sir?

364
00:42:48,650 --> 00:42:50,902
I saw your reaction to the news.

365
00:42:52,862 --> 00:42:54,990
Do you know the woman who died?

366
00:42:55,782 --> 00:42:59,411
I have a copy of the receipt
of her takeout order from this restaurant.

367
00:43:00,203 --> 00:43:03,456
It's my sister who really works here.

368
00:43:03,540 --> 00:43:06,668
I fill in for her
when she's not available.

369
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:08,712
So, you don't know the woman?

370
00:43:08,795 --> 00:43:10,922
Are you a cop, sir?

371
00:43:11,756 --> 00:43:15,885
-Do you know anything?
-I don't know if it matters.

372
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:22,726
-What's your name?
-Hans. Hans Leano.

373
00:43:22,809 --> 00:43:27,063
-When do you fill in for your sister?
-It varies, sir.

374
00:43:27,147 --> 00:43:32,902
but I was working a shift when the teacher
got into an argument with someone.

375
00:43:34,279 --> 00:43:35,447
An argument?

376
00:43:36,698 --> 00:43:37,741
When?

377
00:43:42,329 --> 00:43:44,956
A few days before she was found dead.

378
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:50,295
Do you know who it was?

379
00:43:51,212 --> 00:43:53,465
I heard the teacher called him…

380
00:43:55,050 --> 00:43:56,301
Anton.

381
00:45:02,325 --> 00:45:03,952
Let's talk outside.

382
00:45:04,494 --> 00:45:06,913
Jackie might come and cause a scene.

383
00:45:26,891 --> 00:45:28,309
Is that what you need?

384
00:45:29,018 --> 00:45:31,521
Is that what you need
to leave my family alone?

385
00:47:04,614 --> 00:47:07,242
My family needs me right now.

386
00:47:07,867 --> 00:47:09,077
Especially Eli.

387
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:13,039
I'll be Eli's tutor for now.

388
00:47:13,831 --> 00:47:16,960
I want to focus on my son.

389
00:47:17,043 --> 00:47:22,048
And as a mother, I can feel
that my son needs me right now.

390
00:47:25,051 --> 00:47:26,970
A week before Ms. Ignacio died,

391
00:47:27,053 --> 00:47:30,807
a guy grabbed her at the back
of the Los Pollos Restaurant

392
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:32,809
and forcibly kissed her.

393
00:47:33,351 --> 00:47:38,606
The witness heard her
call the guy "Anton".
